para.para.body:
The shear transformation 
                           S
                         leaves the basic vectors 
                           \StdBss{1}
                         and 
                           \StdBss{2}
                         unchanged, and transforms 
                           \StdBss{3}
                         into 
                           (-3,-1,1)
                        . Therefore it is represented by the matrix 
                           \Mtrx{A}
                         below.

The reflection 
                           R
                         through the origin sends every vector 
                           \Vect{x}
                         to 
                           -\Vect{x}
                        . Therefore it is represented by the matrix 
                           \Mtrx{B}
                         below.
